{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17519887","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17519887"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T14:17:38+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T14:17:38+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13100"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"13100","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/13100"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.06,0.47,0.07,0.35,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5537"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"103348"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"5537","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/5537"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13100"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85768"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"27"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1931"},{"type":"tags","id":"2286"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"2589"},{"type":"tags","id":"3549"},{"type":"tags","id":"3887"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"4982"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"9399"},{"type":"contributions","id":"9724"},{"type":"contributions","id":"36630"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43385"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44736"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"103348","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/103348"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 72-year-old man presents with an eight month history of increasing shortness of breath on exertion, lethargy, and weight loss. He does not have any other health issues. He is a non-smoker, drinks about a can of beer a day and does not use any medications. He worked as a dockyard plumber before retiring eight years ago. On examination, he appears slightly short of breath and clinically anaemic. There are decreased breath sounds over the left basal zone, with stony dullness on percussion in this same region.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA chest X-ray is performed (Image). Clear fluid is obtained from a diagnostic tap and nothing abnormal is found on culture or cytological examination. A subsequent CT scan shows an area of minor pleural thickening.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate diagnostic investigation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Repeat effusion fluid cytology","Video-assisted thoracoscopy (VATS)-guided biopsy","Positron emission tomography (PET)","CT-guided biopsy","Pulmonary function tests"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis case is very suggestive of a \u003Cstrong\u003Emalignant pleural mesothelioma (MPM)\u003C/strong\u003E, a rare neoplasm that originates from the mesothelial surfaces of the pleural cavity. MPM is characterised by its insidious onset and poor prognosis. The primary cause of mesothelioma is occupational asbestos exposure, with professions like construction workers, industrial workers involved in the production of brake pads or insulators and shipyard workers being particularly at risk. While the severity of asbestosis is correlated with the duration of exposure, mesothelioma can develop even with limited exposure.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPatients with MPM typically present with non-specific symptoms such as dyspnoea, non-productive cough and chest pain. Pleural effusions are common and can obscure small pleural or chest lesions on plain X-ray imaging. CT scans of the chest are more sensitive and can detect pleural-based nodularity or pleural plaques.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA biopsy is necessary to confirm the diagnosis of MPM. In this particular case, the most suitable approach would be \u003Cstrong\u003Evideo-assisted thoracoscopy (VATS)-guided biopsy\u003C/strong\u003E, which allows for extensive inspection of the pleura and the collection of multiple large biopsies to assess invasion histologically.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003ECT-guided core biopsy\u003C/strong\u003E is an excellent alternative, but may be more appropriate in cases where imaging studies have revealed focussed areas of significant pleural thickening or a clearly defined mass lesion.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEffusion fluid cytology\u003C/strong\u003E is commonly performed as part of the workup for MPM. However, its role in diagnosing MPM remains a controversial topic due to its inability to assess invasion and its relatively low sensitivity. For confirmed cases of MPM, it is advisable to perform a \u003Cstrong\u003Epositron emission tomography (PET) \u003C/strong\u003Escan to stage the disease and detect any metastases. \u003Cstrong\u003EPulmonary function tests\u003C/strong\u003E, such as FEV1 and DLCO, should be offered to all patients scheduled for surgical resection to ensure sufficient post-surgery lung function.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Malignant pleural mesothelioma (MPM) is a rare neoplasm strongly associated with asbestos exposure.","In a suspected case of MPM, the typical sequence of investigations involves initial imaging studies, such as a CXR or CT scan, followed by aspiration of effusion fluid, and ultimately, confirmation of the diagnosis through VAT-guided biopsy."],"references":["Organising Committee. Guidelines for the Diagnosis and Treatment of Malignant Pleural Mesothelioma [Internet]. Sydney: Asbestos Diseases Research Institute; 2013 [cited 2023 Jun 29]. 116 p. Available from: https://adri.org.au/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Guidelines-for-the-diagnosis-and-treatment-of-malignant-pleural-mesothelioma.pdf","Mott FE. Mesothelioma: a review. Ochsner J [Internet]. 2012 Mar 20 [cited 2023 Jun 29];12(1):70-9. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3307510/","Popat S, Baas P, Faivre-Finn C, Girard N, Nicholson AG, Nowak AK, et al. Malignant pleural mesothelioma: ESMO Clinical Practice Guidelines for diagnosis, treatment and follow-up. Ann Oncol [Internet]. 2022 Feb 1 [cited 2023 Jun 29];33(2):129-42. Available from: https://www.annalsofoncology.org/article/S0923-7534(21)04820-1/fulltext doi: 10.1016/j.annonc.2021.11.005"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85768"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13100"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"20257"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"20257","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/20257"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/T8zkj63XEX1QXSIzN9t9U65hMmLlvz.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/T8zkj63XEX1QXSIzN9t9U65hMmLlvz.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":529,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85768","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/85768"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-05-21T14:57:05+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-21T14:57:31+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5537"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"103348"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"11","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec1","name":"Respiratory Medicine","synonyms":["Pulmonology"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"27","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/ta